Arkansas Governor Asa Hutchinson signed a new religious freedom bill into law on Thursday night . 
  Indiana Governor Mike Pence also signed an amended measure Thursday evening . 
  The two states were at the center of a national uproar over legislation that critics said legalized discrimination on the basis of sexual orientation . 
  Arkansas Governor Hutchinson rejected a previous version of the legislation on Wednesday . 
  The Arkansas legislation was amended to include safeguards against discrimination in the workplace . 
  'Now that this is behind us, let's move forward together with a renewed commitment to the civility and respect that make this state great,' Indiana Governor Pence said after signing his state's amended measure . 
 